properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 9 at 8:38AM CST until January 9 at 12:00PM CST by NWS La Crosse WI
properties.description:
...Slick Travel With a Light Wintry Mix Today...

.A light wintry mix, including freezing rain, is occurring across
portions of southeast Minnesota, northeast Iowa, and western
Wisconsin this morning. Untreated roads and sidewalks will become
slick with a light glazing of ice. If you have travel planned
today, slow down and be prepared for slippery conditions.

* WHAT...Freezing rain. Additional ice accumulations of a light
glaze.

* WHERE...Portions of central, southwest and west central
Wisconsin, northeast Iowa and southeast Minnesota.

* WHEN...Until noon CST today.

* IMPACTS...Any untreated sidewalks, roads and bridges will become
slippery.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling. Prepare for possible
power outages.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST TODAY
